reviews.review: Pretty disappointing. It was like the return of the Jedi, but more boring. Shame.
The ending could of been better, other than that, it was the Star wars.
Great way to end the Skywalker saga. it pays respect to the Actors  and the characters they helped create.
Plot was a mess and had no coherence. As a trilogy this new series did not add to or "close out" the saga in any satisfying way.

I'd chiefly recommend seeing it just so you can know how the current series of Star Wars films ends, so you're in the loop when they inevitably make the next episodes. It truly isnt as bad as most reviews suggest, but it has glaring plot holes, awkward character placement, and some odd storylines that never saw fruition. Acting, cinematography, and score could not be more perfect. This film is lacking in its writing and simply just needed a more logical flow
A beautiful film! All of the heart, humour and action of Star Wars. Bravo

Pacing reflected how badly Disney needed to finish the series so naturally it was awful. Everything was comically convenient when there was a need or roadblock. Character arcs: what are those? And the Force can do exactly whatever the plot needs. I feel bad for JJ Abrams (sorta) for having to clean up the utter mess Rian Johnson left behind. At least it wasn't painfully dull and slow like the Prequels, but that ain't saying much. At least we can all finally put the series to rest and feel free to be disappointed with other Disney products now. That's a silver lining, right?
A good finish to a out of order sequel.

Too many holes in the story, plot elements felt rushed, but special effects were awesome. Tried too hard to be PC and it just made everything feel like they were forcing it down our throats. Very inconsistent with cannon.

The trilogy ended in the only possible way. I like how the characters developed. The actors did a really good job at portraying their emotions thoughts and in general their characters. While the storyline was mostly predictable or at least not very surprising, I still liked it and there were still a few surprises. Most movies have very predictable storylines nowadays.
